sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Browser (SPA)
    participant Cognito as AWS Cognito
    participant IdP as IdP (Entra ID)
    participant PostAuth as PostAuthFederationLink Lambda
    participant PreToken as PreTokenGeneration Lambda
    participant Django as Django Backend

    Note over Browser,Django: Migration — first OIDC login. User not yet in Cognito.<br/>OIDC provider already registered in Cognito (OidcIdentityProvider in SAM template).<br/>No discovery step — frontend redirects directly to Cognito.

    Note over Browser: Generate PKCE pair:<br/>code_verifier = random(32 bytes base64url)<br/>code_challenge = BASE64URL(SHA256(code_verifier))<br/>state = random nonce<br/>Store in sessionStorage: state, code_verifier, provider_type="OIDC"

    Browser->>Cognito: GET /oauth2/authorize<br/>?identity_provider=EntraOidc<br/>&response_type=code<br/>&client_id=X&redirect_uri=callback_url<br/>&scope=openid+email+profile<br/>&state=nonce&code_challenge=Z&code_challenge_method=S256
    Note over Cognito: Validate client + redirect_uri.<br/>Look up EntraOidc OIDC provider.<br/>Build IdP /authorize request with Cognito's own client_id + redirect_uri.
    Cognito-->>Browser: 302 Location: https://login.microsoftonline.com/<tenant>/oauth2/v2.0/authorize?...

    Browser->>IdP: GET /authorize (redirect to IdP login page)
    Note over IdP: User authenticates.<br/>IdP validates identity.
    IdP-->>Cognito: 302 /oauth2/idpresponse?code=IDP_CODE&state=...
    Note over Cognito: Exchange IDP_CODE for id_token with IdP.<br/>Validate id_token: signature, issuer, audience.<br/>Extract email from id_token claims.<br/>Create federated Cognito user (providerType=OIDC).<br/>Generate authorization code.
    Cognito-->>Browser: 302 Location: callback_url?code=AUTH_CODE&state=nonce

    Note over Browser: Assert state == sessionStorage.federated_auth_nonce

    Browser->>Cognito: POST /oauth2/token<br/>grant_type=authorization_code&code=AUTH_CODE<br/>&redirect_uri=callback_url&client_id=X&code_verifier=VERIFIER
    Note over Cognito: Verify code_verifier against stored code_challenge.<br/>Trigger PostAuthentication Lambda.
    Cognito->>PostAuth: PostAuthentication event<br/>userAttributes={email, sub, identities:[{providerType:OIDC, providerName:EntraOidc}]}

    Note over PostAuth: _is_federated_login() = true (providerType=OIDC)<br/>Extract email + Cognito sub.
    PostAuth->>Django: GET /api/internal/user-lookup/?email=user@example.com
    Django-->>PostAuth: 200 {"id":42,"email":"user@example.com"}
    PostAuth->>Django: POST /api/internal/link-cognito/<br/>{"django_user_id":42,"cognito_user_id":"sub-uuid","email":"user@example.com"}
    Django-->>PostAuth: 200 {"linked":true}
    PostAuth->>Cognito: AdminUpdateUserAttributes custom:django_id="42"

    Note over Cognito: Trigger PreTokenGeneration before issuing tokens.
    Cognito->>PreToken: PreTokenGeneration event<br/>userAttributes={email, sub, identities:[OIDC]}<br/>(custom:django_id absent — snapshot taken before PostAuth write)
    Note over PreToken: _login_method() returns "oidc" + "EntraOidc"
    PreToken->>Django: POST /api/internal/login-access-check/<br/>{"email":"user@...","login_method":"oidc","provider_name":"EntraOidc"}
    Django-->>PreToken: 200 {"allowed":true,"django_id":"42"}
    Note over PreToken: django_id="42" received in access-check response.<br/>No separate resolve-django-id call needed.
    PreToken-->>Cognito: claimsToAddOrOverride={django_id:"42"}

    Cognito-->>Browser: 200 {id_token, access_token, refresh_token}
    Note over Browser: OIDC login complete. Tokens stored.
